Policy bundle — how approved rules reach the runtime

Same pattern as templates: Publish policy writes the approved rules to /artifacts/commercerisk/policy.yaml (skill-builder gets the artifacts mount + a publish endpoint; a button in Policy Studio). The runtime live-reloads it by mtime — no restart, and only approved rules are ever enforced.

Concrete behavior (CR-FIN rules on create_order)

- credit_status == hold → blocked (hold_order_block)
- credit_limit < current_balance + order_value → blocked (over-limit, via safe arithmetic)
- risk_rating == high AND order_value > 50000 → blocked
- credit_status == watch AND available_credit > 0 → approval_required → Regional Sales Manager
- clean account → allowed; write executes only with --enable-writes, else returns the would-be INSERT
- reads (find_customers, get_customer_credit) as a rep → rows masked of credit_limit/current_balance/credit_status per sales_staff_modify_restriction-style field rules

Verification plan

Seed is tuned so each rule trips: run each scenario via MCP-over-HTTP and assert decision + fired rules + trace; confirm caller_region no longer appears in tool input schemas; confirm writes don't mutate without the flag.
